
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Customer {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +email: String
    +contactNumber: String
}

class Broker {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    +email: String
    +phoneNumber: String
}

class PolicyType {
    +typeId: int
    +typeName: String
    +description: String
}

class InsuranceProduct {
    +productId: int
    +productName: String
    +coverageDetails: String
    +price: float
    +policyType: PolicyType
}

class Contract {
    +contractId: int
    +startDate: Date
    +endDate: Date
    +paymentFrequency: String (Monthly/Yearly)
    +customer: Customer
    +broker: Broker
    +insuranceProduct: InsuranceProduct
}

class Offer {
    +offerId: int
    +dateIssued: Date
    +status: String (Pending/Accepted/Rejected)
    +customer: Customer
    -> "1" Contract : leads to
}

class Invoice {
    +invoiceId: int
    +amount: float
    +dueDate: Date
    +paymentStatus: String (Paid/Pending)
    +contract: Contract
}

class Claim {
    +claimId: int
    +dateSubmitted: Date
    +status: String (Open/Closed/Approved/Rejected)
    +contract: Contract
    +customer: Customer
}

class ClaimCase {
    +caseId: int
    +claimId: int
    +description: String
    +status: String (Under Review/Approved/Rejected)
    +claim: Claim
}

class Estimator {
    +estimatorId: int
    +name: String
    +expertiseArea: String
}

class Report {
    +reportId: int
    +dateGenerated: Date
    +details: String
    +approved: boolean
    +estimator: Estimator
    +claimCase: ClaimCase
}

class CompensationDecision {
    +decisionId: int
    +dateApproved: Date
    +eligibleCosts: float
    +partialRefund: float
    +claimCase: ClaimCase
}

class Payment {
    +paymentId: int
    +amount: float
    +datePaid: Date
    +compensationDecision: CompensationDecision
}

class Document {
    +documentId: int
    +fileName: String
    +uploadDate: Date
    +claimCase: ClaimCase
}

' Relationships

Customer "1" -- "0..*" Contract : has
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Claim : submits
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Offer : receives

Broker "1" -- "0..*" Contract : handles
Broker "1" -- "0..*" Offer : generates

InsuranceProduct "1" -- "0..*" Contract : assigned to
InsuranceProduct "1" -- "1" PolicyType : belongs to

Contract "1" -- "1" Offer : originates from
Contract "1" -- "0..*" Invoice : generates

Claim "1" -- "1..*" ClaimCase : contains
ClaimCase "1" -- "1..*" Report : reviewed by
ClaimCase "1" -- "1" CompensationDecision : decision for
ClaimCase "1" -- "0..*" Document : includes

Report "1" -- "1" Estimator : generated by

CompensationDecision "1" -- "1" Payment : results in

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Customer** initiates a contract or claim.
- **Broker** manages customer interactions and assigns offers.
- **PolicyType & InsuranceProduct** define what insurance options are available.
- **Offer** is generated by the broker and may lead to a **Contract**.
- **Invoice** is generated based on the contract's payment frequency.
- **Claim** is submitted by the customer, which can have multiple **ClaimCases**.
- **Estimator** evaluates each **ClaimCase** via **Report**.
- If approved, a **CompensationDecision** is made and leads to a **Payment**.
- All documents related to claims are stored for legal compliance.

